WEBVTT

00:01.710 --> 00:03.795
♪ ♪

00:06.214 --> 00:08.258
(jaunty music playing)

00:23.440 --> 00:25.275
{\an8}<i>WARM FEMALE VOICE:</i>
<i>Your husband saw them</i>

00:25.358 --> 00:27.110
{\an8}<i>take a baby out of there.</i>

00:27.193 --> 00:29.612
{\an8}<i>And now he needs help.</i>

00:29.696 --> 00:31.114
{\an8}(R&amp;B music playing)

00:31.197 --> 00:33.616
{\an8}<i>Side effects may include</i>
<i>dry mouth,</i>

00:33.700 --> 00:36.995
{\an8}<i>fatigue, headaches,</i>
<i>rage, melancholy...</i>

00:37.078 --> 00:39.664
<i>Go to your assigned</i>
<i>fulfillment center</i>

00:39.748 --> 00:41.916
<i>-to receive your family's EGG.</i>
-(jaunty music playing)

00:42.000 --> 00:43.334
<i>Bring it home,</i>

00:43.418 --> 00:45.628
<i>and let us take care</i>
<i>of the rest.</i>

00:45.712 --> 00:48.631
<i>The EGG will make everything</i>
<i>okay again</i>

00:48.715 --> 00:52.677
<i>and this time</i>
<i>it will be okay forever.</i>

00:52.761 --> 00:54.679
{\an8}(whooshing)

00:54.763 --> 00:57.140
{\an8}-(birds chirping)
-(electronic warbling)

00:57.223 --> 00:59.225
{\an8}(clock ticking)

01:02.061 --> 01:03.938
(gasps)

01:04.022 --> 01:06.024
♪ ♪

01:09.903 --> 01:11.321
(sighs)

01:21.581 --> 01:23.208
Goddamn it.

01:24.250 --> 01:26.252
(soft electrical buzzing)

01:34.761 --> 01:36.763
(sniffing)

01:44.437 --> 01:46.064
(sniffs, gasps)

01:56.282 --> 01:58.076
-(birds chirping)
-(clock ticking)

02:04.123 --> 02:06.334
(sniffing)

02:09.545 --> 02:11.589
(sniffing)

02:15.760 --> 02:17.720
<i>(doorbell rings)</i>

02:17.804 --> 02:20.056
{\an5}<i>MRS. JONES:</i>
<i>What do you mean,</i>
<i>you're losing time?</i>

02:20.139 --> 02:23.101
You, like, blacking out
completely or--

02:23.184 --> 02:24.853
I don't know-- browning out?

02:26.479 --> 02:29.899
You don't think
it could be odorless, do you?

02:29.983 --> 02:33.236
Or could you be, like--
I don't know-- fainting?

02:33.319 --> 02:36.447
I used to faint kind of
all the time in college.

02:36.531 --> 02:39.450
No, no, no,
I'm whooshing lightly.

02:39.534 --> 02:41.244
Fainting is down.

02:41.327 --> 02:43.705
This is up, like a-a floating.

02:43.788 --> 02:46.875
A... a whooshing floating.

02:46.958 --> 02:49.085
And it's happened
more than once?

02:49.168 --> 02:52.088
It happens at regular intervals.

02:52.171 --> 02:56.718
I'll just be going about my day,
and then I hear this music,

02:56.801 --> 02:58.928
a short sequence of chords,

02:59.012 --> 03:03.099
and then a kind of lightness,
a whooshing.

03:03.182 --> 03:05.810
And then, all of a sudden,

03:05.894 --> 03:08.229
the next thing I know,
I'm waking up.

03:08.313 --> 03:09.898
Up there.

03:09.981 --> 03:11.733
Up in my bedroom.

03:14.193 --> 03:16.613
I used to think your kitchen
got better light than mine,

03:16.696 --> 03:18.448
but now I don't think it does.

03:19.657 --> 03:21.951
And you chose these countertops

03:22.035 --> 03:24.621
on purpose or...?

03:24.704 --> 03:27.749
(scoffs)
God, if I could strike a match

03:27.832 --> 03:30.627
and burn the whole place down,
I would.

03:30.710 --> 03:32.545
Start all over again.

03:34.213 --> 03:37.133
Would be something to do.
Right?

03:37.216 --> 03:40.470
Unless you think
it's a brain tumor.

03:40.553 --> 03:42.013
You don't think?

03:42.096 --> 03:45.016
Well, did you call someone
to take a look at it?

03:45.099 --> 03:48.436
You know, a handyman
or whatever his name is.

03:48.519 --> 03:51.105
What is he gonna look at?
What is there to see?

03:51.189 --> 03:53.858
It could be odorless
<i>and</i> colorless.

03:53.942 --> 03:56.653
Oh, well, what did your phone
say about it?

03:58.613 --> 04:00.239
I just...

04:01.699 --> 04:04.160
I need you to be here
when it happens,

04:04.243 --> 04:06.371
to watch
and tell me what happens.

04:06.454 --> 04:08.373
Can you do that?

04:08.456 --> 04:11.501
My allotted fulfillment hour
is at 1:00.

04:11.584 --> 04:13.628
Oh. Right.

04:13.711 --> 04:16.047
Do you think I should go to
my assigned fulfillment center

04:16.130 --> 04:17.966
at 12:30 or 12:00?

04:18.048 --> 04:20.551
They'll probably put us
in a line, I guess.

04:20.635 --> 04:22.553
Is yours earlier?
Yours isn't earlier.

04:22.637 --> 04:25.306
No, I-I'm not until 4:00.

04:25.390 --> 04:28.393
4:00? (scoffs)

04:28.476 --> 04:31.312
How do you even begin to wait?

04:31.396 --> 04:34.565
You don't seem excited.
Are you excited?

04:34.649 --> 04:38.111
No. I am. I am.

04:38.194 --> 04:41.197
But you do still want it,
don't you?

04:41.281 --> 04:43.366
Yes, I... No.

04:43.449 --> 04:45.660
More than anything.

04:45.743 --> 04:47.203
Yeah.

04:47.286 --> 04:49.497
It'll be just like
the commercials say.

04:49.580 --> 04:52.834
"Your family's EGG
will make everything okay again,

04:52.917 --> 04:56.337
and this time, it'll make
everything okay forever."

04:57.797 --> 05:01.551
Don't you just wish
they'd show it to us?

05:01.634 --> 05:03.553
You know, a peek at this thing

05:03.636 --> 05:06.389
that's supposed
to change our lives.

05:06.472 --> 05:08.891
Mm, it'll be so great
if it somehow helps

05:08.975 --> 05:13.271
with Xerxes' babysitting anxiety
or Xander's biting thing.

05:13.354 --> 05:14.981
Oh. Oh, did Rex end up

05:15.064 --> 05:17.358
liking his medication,
or not so much?

05:17.442 --> 05:18.735
Shh!

05:18.818 --> 05:20.695
(clock ticking)

05:20.778 --> 05:22.697
Hold on.

05:22.780 --> 05:24.824
I think it might...

05:24.907 --> 05:27.118
♪ ♪

05:32.165 --> 05:34.083
Submitted for your approval:

05:34.167 --> 05:36.711
Mrs. Janet Warren,

05:36.794 --> 05:39.422
a woman who would seem
to have everything.

05:39.505 --> 05:42.925
Every...<i> thing.</i>

05:43.009 --> 05:45.553
But possessions have weight.

05:45.636 --> 05:48.681
We can't carry them all
at the same time,

05:48.765 --> 05:52.435
especially when taking
an unscheduled trip

05:52.518 --> 05:55.438
into The Twilight Zone.

05:55.521 --> 05:57.523
(electronic chords playing)

05:59.525 --> 06:01.527
(deep whoosh, click)

06:03.529 --> 06:05.114
<i>(The Twilight Zone</i> theme
playing)

06:05.198 --> 06:06.741
<i>NARRATOR: You're traveling</i>
<i>through another dimension,</i>

06:06.824 --> 06:10.203
<i>a dimension not only of</i>
<i>sight and sound but of mind.</i>

06:10.286 --> 06:13.456
<i>It is the middle ground</i>
<i>between light and shadow,</i>

06:13.539 --> 06:16.167
<i>between science</i>
<i>and superstition.</i>

06:16.250 --> 06:18.795
{\an8}<i>And it lies between</i>
<i>the pit of one's fears</i>

06:18.878 --> 06:21.631
{\an8}<i>and the summit</i>
<i>of one's knowledge.</i>

06:21.714 --> 06:24.801
<i>You are now traveling through</i>
<i>a dimension of imagination.</i>

06:24.884 --> 06:28.763
<i>You've just crossed over</i>
<i>into The Twilight Zone.</i>

06:33.059 --> 06:34.852
{\an8}(birds chirping)

06:36.771 --> 06:37.980
{\an8}(sighs):
Ah.

06:39.190 --> 06:41.984
{\an8}Dad, what's "immolation" mean?

06:42.068 --> 06:44.654
{\an8}Well...

06:44.737 --> 06:47.031
{\an8}that's certainly a big word.

06:47.115 --> 06:49.659
{\an8}But I'll tell you.

06:49.742 --> 06:52.161
{\an8}You remember our neighbor
Don Parker?

06:53.412 --> 06:55.957
{\an8}Well, instead of
having a garage sale,

06:56.040 --> 06:58.334
{\an8}he just lit a match to his house

06:58.417 --> 07:02.964
{\an8}and burned everything
and everyone to the ground.

07:03.047 --> 07:05.007
{\an8}And that was that--

07:05.091 --> 07:09.137
{\an8}a fresh, clean start
for Don Parker.

07:09.220 --> 07:11.764
{\an8}But why do you ask, Billy?

07:11.848 --> 07:16.060
{\an8}Is there something or someone
you want to immolate?

07:20.064 --> 07:23.526
{\an8}Mm. I get it.

07:23.609 --> 07:25.528
{\an8}I really do.

07:25.611 --> 07:27.697
{\an8}But we can't all be
Don Parker, son.

07:27.780 --> 07:32.827
{\an8}But, you know,
there is a place we can go.

07:32.910 --> 07:35.705
{\an8}<i>WARM FEMALE VOICE:</i>
<i>Come on over to</i>

07:35.788 --> 07:40.334
{\an8}<i>the Immolation Station, where</i>
<i>you get to play with matches,</i>

07:40.418 --> 07:42.545
{\an8}<i>-and you get</i>
<i>to watch it all burn.</i>
-(fire roars)

07:42.628 --> 07:44.172
{\an8}-(laughs)
-MAN: Fire.

07:44.255 --> 07:46.382
{\an8}-WOMAN: Hey.
<i>-WARM FEMALE VOICE:</i>
<i>Don't forget,</i>

07:46.465 --> 07:49.677
{\an8}<i>every Wednesday, kids eat free.</i>

07:49.760 --> 07:52.221
{\an8}(piano playing gentle melody)

07:52.305 --> 07:55.391
{\an8}<i>It's</i> your <i> EGG,</i>

07:55.474 --> 08:00.396
{\an8}<i>and you want it</i>
<i>more than anything.</i>

08:05.610 --> 08:07.570
{\an8}-(birds chirping)
-(clock ticking)

08:14.827 --> 08:16.746
{\an8}(dog barking in distance)

08:16.829 --> 08:19.415
{\an8}What happened?

08:19.498 --> 08:22.126
{\an8}Is this...
is this what's happening?

08:22.210 --> 08:24.295
{\an8}Did you hear the music?

08:28.341 --> 08:30.343
{\an8}Is this your bedroom?

08:31.636 --> 08:34.222
{\an8}I like the patterning.
It's brave.

08:38.017 --> 08:40.686
{\an8}-How did we get up here?
-Join the club.

08:40.770 --> 08:42.230
{\an8}Did I faint?

08:42.313 --> 08:45.358
{\an8}Did I hit my head?
Did we hit our heads?

08:48.027 --> 08:49.487
{\an8}(gasps) What time is it?

08:49.570 --> 08:51.948
{\an8}Did we...? (gasps)

08:52.031 --> 08:53.783
{\an8}I really ought to

08:53.866 --> 08:57.286
{\an8}get out of here--
I-I mean, oh, get going.

08:57.370 --> 08:59.497
{\an8}I saw the EGG.

08:59.580 --> 09:00.665
{\an8}Huh?

09:01.707 --> 09:03.292
{\an8}The EGG.

09:03.376 --> 09:06.545
{\an8}I'm telling you, I saw it.

09:06.629 --> 09:07.964
{\an8}Oh, well, no.

09:08.047 --> 09:09.382
{\an8}(chuckles) You couldn't have.

09:09.465 --> 09:11.467
{\an8}No, you didn't.

09:13.427 --> 09:15.304
{\an8}What do you mean
you just saw it?

09:15.388 --> 09:17.306
{\an8}Just now? Where? Was I there?

09:17.390 --> 09:20.101
{\an8}I don't know. It was like
I saw it in a commercial,

09:20.184 --> 09:22.645
{\an8}like a commercial
in my head, I guess.

09:22.728 --> 09:26.607
{\an8}I don't know. I just know
that I've seen one.

09:29.235 --> 09:30.820
{\an8}It's ugly.

09:30.903 --> 09:32.446
{\an8}Ugly, no.

09:32.530 --> 09:34.156
{\an8}(chuckles softly)

09:34.240 --> 09:36.033
{\an8}Yeah, I doubt that very much.

09:36.117 --> 09:37.827
{\an8}They wouldn't go
to all the trouble

09:37.910 --> 09:39.829
{\an8}to design and make something

09:39.912 --> 09:43.124
{\an8}that's, you know,
that's for all of us,

09:43.207 --> 09:47.128
{\an8}that will be the centerpiece
for every American home,

09:47.211 --> 09:48.963
{\an8}and then make it ugly.

09:49.046 --> 09:50.673
{\an8}No.

09:50.756 --> 09:52.675
{\an8}But don't you see

09:52.758 --> 09:56.846
{\an8}that none of us even knows
what it is or what it does?

09:56.929 --> 09:58.848
{\an8}Don't you think it's strange

09:58.931 --> 10:01.851
{\an8}that all we know is
that we have to have one,

10:01.934 --> 10:04.020
{\an8}everyone has to have one?

10:04.103 --> 10:05.313
{\an8}Strange?
What makes it so strange?

10:05.396 --> 10:09.859
{\an8}What if it has something to do
with whatever's happening to me?

10:09.942 --> 10:12.236
{\an8}The EGG.

10:12.320 --> 10:16.532
{\an8}What if it has something to do
with whatever's happening to us?

10:16.615 --> 10:18.159
{\an8}Oh, no.

10:18.242 --> 10:21.537
{\an8}(laughs)
No, no, no.

10:21.620 --> 10:25.499
{\an8}Don't include me in whatever
is happening here with you.

10:25.583 --> 10:28.544
{\an8}I just came over here
as a good neighbor to see

10:28.627 --> 10:30.713
{\an8}if there's anything
I can do to help you.

10:30.796 --> 10:35.760
{\an8}We might have
a <i> lot</i> of the same things,

10:35.843 --> 10:38.929
{\an8}but we don't have
the same problems.

10:39.013 --> 10:41.390
{\an8}We just woke up on my bed

10:41.474 --> 10:43.392
{\an8}with our shoes on.

10:43.476 --> 10:45.227
{\an8}I have a twig in my hair.

10:45.311 --> 10:47.063
{\an8}That wasn't there
when you came in

10:47.146 --> 10:49.440
{\an8}and we were talking earlier,
was it?

10:49.523 --> 10:52.943
{\an8}I-I don't know if it was there
or if it wasn't.

10:53.027 --> 10:54.862
{\an8}I just know that

10:54.945 --> 10:57.073
{\an8}my hour of fulfillment is gonna
be here before I know it,

10:57.156 --> 10:59.408
{\an8}and I really ought
to be home, so...

10:59.492 --> 11:00.910
Thank you.

11:00.993 --> 11:02.078
Okay.

11:02.161 --> 11:04.038
-No! Wait!
-(laughs)

11:04.121 --> 11:05.414
Are you touching me?

11:05.498 --> 11:07.124
What if they're connected?

11:07.208 --> 11:09.752
The EGG and the...
the rushing, rising whooshing?

11:09.835 --> 11:11.087
Ow! You're hurting me.

11:11.170 --> 11:13.047
Something is happening here,

11:13.130 --> 11:15.800
and you don't know what it is,
either, do you, Mrs. Jones?

11:15.883 --> 11:17.426
I just want to be
at my fulfillment center

11:17.510 --> 11:19.136
at my fulfillment hour
to collect my family's EGG

11:19.220 --> 11:21.430
-like a normal person.
-No!

11:21.514 --> 11:23.265
(yelling)

11:23.349 --> 11:26.102
-No!
-(yelling)

11:26.185 --> 11:29.480
(groans)

11:29.563 --> 11:31.440
We do <i> not</i> have
the same problems!

11:31.524 --> 11:33.776
(cries)

11:33.859 --> 11:35.486
(sighs)

11:35.569 --> 11:37.822
(door opens, closes)

11:48.457 --> 11:49.959
(sniffles)

12:01.721 --> 12:04.265
-(line ringing)
<i>-MEGHAN: Dick Warren's office.</i>

12:04.348 --> 12:05.850
<i>This is Meghan.</i>

12:05.933 --> 12:07.977
Hi, Meghan. It's Jane.

12:08.060 --> 12:09.812
Is my husband there?

12:09.895 --> 12:12.356
<i>Hi there, Mrs. Warren.</i>
<i>I'm so sorry.</i>

12:12.440 --> 12:14.358
<i>Mr. Warren is in a meeting.</i>

12:14.442 --> 12:16.652
<i>Is there a message</i>
<i>you'd like me to give him?</i>

12:16.735 --> 12:20.114
Oh, honestly, Meghan,
I can't imagine.

12:20.197 --> 12:22.450
<i>He did want to make sure</i>

12:22.533 --> 12:25.202
<i>that I remind you</i>
<i>that your allotted hour</i>

12:25.286 --> 12:26.662
<i>of fulfillment is 4:00 p.m....</i>

12:26.745 --> 12:28.497
Uh-huh. Yeah, I know.

12:28.581 --> 12:30.666
<i>You don't seem excited,</i>
<i>Mrs. Warren.</i>

12:30.750 --> 12:32.501
<i>-Aren't you excited?</i>
-(cabinet door closes)

12:32.585 --> 12:36.172
Tell me something, Meghan.

12:36.255 --> 12:39.383
Why do you want
your family's EGG?

12:39.467 --> 12:41.844
<i>Uh... because</i>

12:41.927 --> 12:44.180
<i>it's coming out?</i>

12:44.263 --> 12:46.891
Of course, but...

12:46.974 --> 12:49.185
But you don't have a family.

12:49.268 --> 12:51.187
Do you?

12:51.270 --> 12:54.356
<i>No, but I do want everything</i>
<i>to be okay again.</i>

12:54.440 --> 12:57.485
<i>And this time</i>
<i>for it to be okay forever.</i>

12:57.568 --> 13:00.279
Because things aren't okay
for you.

13:00.362 --> 13:02.531
<i>Oh, for me?</i>
<i>Things are cool.</i>

13:02.615 --> 13:06.368
<i>But, like, for the</i> world <i> world</i>
<i>out there, outside of me?</i>

13:06.452 --> 13:08.370
Outside of you, sure.

13:08.454 --> 13:13.167
<i>Um, Mrs. Warren, things are</i>
<i>really, definitely</i> not,

13:13.250 --> 13:15.044
<i>like, in the</i> world <i> world.</i>

13:15.127 --> 13:16.879
<i>So definitely</i> not <i> okay.</i>

13:16.962 --> 13:19.215
<i>Like, not at all, not at all.</i>

13:19.298 --> 13:23.052
<i>I mean, have you seen what all</i>
<i>these human beings are doing?</i>

13:23.135 --> 13:25.221
Interesting.

13:25.304 --> 13:28.682
So you think it's something
for the whole planet?

13:28.766 --> 13:31.644
<i>Don't you think it'd better be,</i>
<i>Mrs. Warren?</i>

13:33.521 --> 13:35.856
<i>Um, Mrs. Warren?</i>

13:35.940 --> 13:38.776
Hmm.

13:38.859 --> 13:41.028
{\an5}<i>AUTOMATED FEMALE VOICE:</i>
<i>Welcome to the EGG</i>
<i>Customer Service Center.</i>

13:41.111 --> 13:42.738
Operator.

13:42.821 --> 13:44.240
<i>Please listen</i>
<i>to the following options.</i>

13:44.323 --> 13:46.075
-Operator.
<i>-If you'd like to confirm</i>

13:46.158 --> 13:48.410
<i>your hour of fulfillment,</i>
<i>please press one.</i>

13:48.494 --> 13:51.580
{\an5}-Human being.
<i>-If you've lost</i>
<i>your registration card,</i>

13:51.664 --> 13:54.250
<i>-please press two.</i>
-Real human being.

13:54.333 --> 13:56.418
<i>If you need to change</i>
<i>the pickup location</i>

13:56.502 --> 13:58.087
<i>-of your EGG...</i>
-Supervisor.

13:58.170 --> 14:01.549
<i>Okay. Supervisor.</i>
<i>Hello. How may we help you?</i>

14:01.632 --> 14:03.551
Yes, yes, hello.

14:03.634 --> 14:05.761
Hi. Thank you.

14:05.844 --> 14:08.597
Uh, yes, uh, well, I was hoping

14:08.681 --> 14:12.977
I could talk to someone
about, you know, the EGG.

14:13.060 --> 14:15.896
I was hoping
there might be someone there

14:15.980 --> 14:17.940
that could tell me
just a little bit more about,

14:18.023 --> 14:20.734
you know, what it is,
what it does.

14:20.818 --> 14:22.653
What it is.

14:22.736 --> 14:23.779
(musical tones sounding)

14:23.862 --> 14:26.156
<i>Okay, I'll transfer you now.</i>

14:26.240 --> 14:27.992
No, no, I don't want
to be tra...

14:28.075 --> 14:29.994
(Muzak playing over phone)

14:30.077 --> 14:32.580
♪ ♪

14:38.252 --> 14:40.296
(tires screeching)

14:46.051 --> 14:47.303
Marge.

14:47.386 --> 14:48.971
God, everything's gonna be okay
this time.

14:49.054 --> 14:50.180
It's gonna be okay forever.

14:50.264 --> 14:52.016
Oh.

14:52.099 --> 14:53.142
Marge Stevens.

14:53.225 --> 14:54.143
What? What?

14:54.226 --> 14:55.769
(gasping)

14:55.853 --> 14:57.146
You got your EGG.

14:57.229 --> 14:58.480
(nervous chuckle)

14:58.564 --> 15:00.608
Can I take a look at it?

15:00.691 --> 15:02.651
No. Huh.

15:02.735 --> 15:04.486
Are you out of your mind?
I have to--

15:04.570 --> 15:07.990
I have to get it inside. Inside.

15:15.247 --> 15:17.708
(line ringing)

15:19.585 --> 15:20.836
<i>WARM FEMALE VOICE:</i>
<i>This is Meghan.</i>

15:20.919 --> 15:23.339
<i>How may we assist you?</i>

15:23.422 --> 15:25.674
Meghan?

15:25.758 --> 15:30.304
Um... Oh, uh, hello.

15:30.387 --> 15:32.848
Hmm. Uh...

15:32.931 --> 15:35.517
this is Jane Warren

15:35.601 --> 15:39.021
of 13182 Teacup Road.

15:39.104 --> 15:42.149
And... well,

15:42.232 --> 15:44.234
I know this might sound strange,

15:44.318 --> 15:48.530
but I was just wondering
if it's still possible

15:48.614 --> 15:52.701
to cancel my family's EGG.

15:52.785 --> 15:54.912
<i>Cancel?</i>

15:54.995 --> 15:56.538
Yes.

15:56.622 --> 15:59.208
I-I mean, you know...

15:59.291 --> 16:01.001
Well-well, you see,
the thing is, I-I just,

16:01.085 --> 16:04.463
I don't, I don't know, you know,
what-what it is, exactly,

16:04.546 --> 16:08.050
or, you know,
what it's supposed to do...

16:08.133 --> 16:09.718
(chuckles)
...exactly.

16:09.802 --> 16:14.098
I mean, you know...

16:15.974 --> 16:18.310
I just changed my mind.

16:20.979 --> 16:23.607
<i>And what is the reason</i>

16:23.691 --> 16:26.193
<i>for the change in your mind?</i>

16:26.276 --> 16:28.195
Well...

16:29.488 --> 16:32.491
I don't want it anymore.

16:33.992 --> 16:38.038
I do-- I don't want
any EGG... anymore.

16:38.122 --> 16:42.084
Uh... thank you, though.

16:42.167 --> 16:43.961
Thank you.

16:44.044 --> 16:46.422
<i>Is there anything else</i>
<i>we can help you with today?</i>

16:46.505 --> 16:50.050
No. Um...

16:50.134 --> 16:51.885
so you did it?

16:51.969 --> 16:55.305
You canceled my order? You-you
canceled my family's EGG?

16:55.389 --> 16:58.934
<i>We are processing your request.</i>

16:59.017 --> 17:01.812
Okay. I see. Um...

17:01.895 --> 17:06.442
so you'll just... confirm

17:06.525 --> 17:07.984
and let me know?

17:08.068 --> 17:11.113
Or... send a confirmation
to my...

17:11.195 --> 17:13.365
(line clicks)

17:30.549 --> 17:32.551
(birds chirping)

17:36.054 --> 17:38.098
(lawnmower running nearby)

18:07.419 --> 18:09.463
(door creaks)

18:28.398 --> 18:30.400
♪ ♪

18:51.296 --> 18:53.298
♪ ♪

19:13.277 --> 19:15.279
♪ ♪

19:37.467 --> 19:39.469
♪ ♪

20:02.326 --> 20:05.662
(jaunty music playing)

20:05.746 --> 20:08.290
{\an5}<i>WARM FEMALE VOICE:</i>
<i>You've suffered</i>
<i>some tough losses,</i>

20:08.373 --> 20:10.792
<i>and no one blames you</i>
<i>for crying in the kitchen</i>

20:10.876 --> 20:14.880
<i>in the middle of the day.</i>

20:18.675 --> 20:21.345
<i>You're heartbroken,</i>

20:21.428 --> 20:25.140
<i>but you know how to choose</i>
<i>your paper towels.</i>

20:25.223 --> 20:28.852
<i>Now with 43% more</i>
<i>clean-up power.</i>

20:36.818 --> 20:38.362
(gasps)

20:42.199 --> 20:44.201
(hissing)

21:01.927 --> 21:05.305
♪ ♪

21:05.389 --> 21:06.932
(gasps)

21:29.079 --> 21:31.373
(birds singing)

21:34.501 --> 21:37.379
(line ringing)

21:37.462 --> 21:40.382
(phone chiming)

21:40.465 --> 21:42.342
(dog barking)

21:46.346 --> 21:49.224
(woman clears throat)

21:51.810 --> 21:54.187
Aquarian Portal,
where we're not happy until

21:54.271 --> 21:56.106
the planets revolve around you.

21:56.189 --> 21:58.734
Shaman-ess Chantal Stargazer
speaking.

21:58.817 --> 22:01.236
<i>How can I better align you</i>
<i>with your cosmic purpose?</i>

22:01.319 --> 22:04.865
Ah, Chantal, thank God.
It's Jane.

22:04.948 --> 22:07.451
Oh... don't aggravate
the marinade.

22:07.534 --> 22:09.369
Jane Warren.

22:09.453 --> 22:13.373
Yes. Yes, yes, oh...

22:13.457 --> 22:15.250
Oh, how magical.

22:15.333 --> 22:19.046
Can we talk for a minute,
I mean, really talk?

22:19.129 --> 22:20.756
<i>-Like real human beings.</i>
-(slurping)

22:20.839 --> 22:22.257
Knock yourself out.

22:22.340 --> 22:24.760
<i>I don't want to</i>
<i>say this out loud, but</i>

22:24.843 --> 22:28.096
I think I might have been,
you know, taken.

22:28.180 --> 22:29.765
(whispers):
Abducted.

22:29.848 --> 22:33.393
-Abducted? By who?
<i>-Do my planets say</i>

22:33.477 --> 22:36.897
anything about any of this
or anything?

22:36.980 --> 22:38.774
The planets say,

22:38.857 --> 22:43.236
<i>"Today all well-worn and trusty</i>
<i>paths are covered over,</i>

22:43.320 --> 22:45.072
<i>"and a new map is drawn.</i>

22:45.155 --> 22:47.949
<i>"Only you have the power</i>
<i>to reroute</i>

22:48.033 --> 22:50.786
<i>"the flow of the river</i>
<i>of space-time.</i>

22:50.869 --> 22:54.372
<i>"Don't let yourself be swept up</i>
<i>by anyone else's dreams.</i>

22:54.456 --> 22:55.665
<i>"Untether yourself.</i>

22:55.749 --> 22:58.585
Resist gravity and fly away."

22:58.668 --> 23:01.963
Resist gravity.

23:02.047 --> 23:04.382
Of course.

23:09.763 --> 23:13.391
Let's see you
beam me up now, Scotty,

23:13.475 --> 23:15.143
or whoever you are.

23:31.743 --> 23:34.329
(breathing deeply)

23:57.102 --> 23:59.396
♪ ♪

24:18.039 --> 24:20.041
♪ ♪

24:33.138 --> 24:36.057
<i>ALL (in unison):</i>
<i>Well, what do we...?</i>

24:36.141 --> 24:40.103
<i>Well... what do...?</i>

24:45.317 --> 24:48.111
<i>KANAMIT 1:</i>
<i>Well, what do we do now?</i>

24:48.195 --> 24:50.947
<i>KANAMIT 2:</i>
<i>Its leg is stuck.</i>

24:51.031 --> 24:53.241
{\an5}<i>KANAMIT 1:</i>
<i>We could take it</i>
<i>without its leg.</i>

24:53.325 --> 24:56.286
<i>KANAMIT 3:</i>
<i>Its leg is its best piece.</i>

24:56.369 --> 25:01.625
{\an5}<i>KANAMIT 1:</i>
<i>Mmm, all of this leg talk</i>
<i>is making me hungry.</i>

25:01.708 --> 25:04.920
{\an5}<i>KANAMIT 2:</i>
<i>Mmm, are we thinking original</i>
<i>recipe or extra crispy?</i>

25:05.003 --> 25:08.757
<i>ALL:</i>
<i>Original recipe it is.</i>

25:10.300 --> 25:12.886
<i>KANAMIT 1:</i>
<i>But we should take a vote.</i>

25:12.969 --> 25:14.554
{\an5}<i>KANAMIT 3:</i>
<i>What is it about</i>
<i>a single shared mind</i>

25:14.638 --> 25:16.431
<i>that he doesn't understand?</i>

25:16.514 --> 25:18.642
{\an5}<i>KANAMIT 1:</i>
<i>Let's be careful</i>
<i>with our pronouns.</i>

25:18.725 --> 25:21.269
{\an5}<i>KANAMIT 2:</i>
<i>He understands everything</i>
<i>that you understand.</i>

25:21.353 --> 25:24.147
{\an5}<i>KANAMIT 1:</i>
We <i> understand everything</i>
<i>that</i> we <i> understand.</i>

25:24.231 --> 25:26.775
<i>KANAMIT 2:</i>
<i>I love us.</i>

25:26.858 --> 25:28.360
<i>KANAMIT 3:</i>
<i>I also love us. That is not...</i>

25:28.443 --> 25:30.028
<i>KANAMIT 1:</i>
We <i> love us.</i>

25:30.111 --> 25:33.365
<i>ALL:</i>
<i>Yes, that really is best.</i>

25:33.448 --> 25:37.327
<i>Well, what do we do now</i>
<i>about the madwoman</i>

25:37.410 --> 25:39.829
<i>in the oxygen tower?</i>

25:45.168 --> 25:48.255
{\an5}<i>KANAMIT 3:</i>
<i>The transfer ray</i>
<i>will wear off soon.</i>

25:48.338 --> 25:50.632
<i>Whatever we do,</i>
<i>we don't want it to wake up.</i>

25:50.715 --> 25:53.260
{\an5}<i>KANAMIT 1:</i>
<i>We are afraid of them</i>
<i>waking up.</i>

25:53.343 --> 25:55.262
{\an5}<i>KANAMIT 3:</i>
<i>Because they have</i>
<i>their own mind.</i>

25:55.345 --> 25:57.806
{\an5}<i>KANAMIT 2:</i>
<i>Their own terrible</i>
<i>desires and wishes.</i>

25:57.889 --> 26:01.226
{\an5}<i>KANAMIT 3:</i>
<i>Their own horrifying lack</i>
<i>of this</i>

26:01.309 --> 26:03.436
<i>-and that.</i>
-Hey!

26:28.211 --> 26:31.339
I said "Hey!"

26:33.717 --> 26:38.346
You can't just pull us out
of our lives, you know.

26:44.227 --> 26:47.605
What, exactly, are you doing
with me, anyway?

26:51.067 --> 26:55.488
{\an5}<i>ALL:</i>
<i>We don't know.</i>
<i>We only work here.</i>

26:57.615 --> 27:00.493
Is there someone I can talk to?

27:00.577 --> 27:05.290
Uh, your... your leader.

27:09.711 --> 27:11.880
Your supervisor.

27:11.963 --> 27:14.716
Take me to your supervisor.

27:23.725 --> 27:26.394
♪ ♪

27:26.478 --> 27:30.231
<i>My name is Janet Warren,</i>
<i>born Janet Davey,</i>

27:30.315 --> 27:33.234
<i>July 7, 1974.</i>

27:33.318 --> 27:37.197
<i>Five-six, 137 pounds.</i>

27:37.280 --> 27:40.700
<i>When I was a little girl,</i>
<i>I got lost in an amusement park</i>

27:40.784 --> 27:43.578
<i>for two hours,</i>
<i>but really I was hiding</i>

27:43.661 --> 27:45.080
<i>in one of the backstage areas</i>

27:45.163 --> 27:49.000
<i>with the mascot</i>
<i>character costumes.</i>

27:49.084 --> 27:50.877
<i>When I was a junior</i>
<i>in high school,</i>

27:50.960 --> 27:53.755
<i>I wanted to be</i>
<i>an Olympic ice skater</i>

27:53.838 --> 27:56.007
<i>or a country-western singer.</i>

27:56.091 --> 27:59.427
<i>But then I was none</i>
<i>of those things.</i>

27:59.511 --> 28:03.598
<i>I'm married.</i>
<i>I have two children.</i>

28:03.681 --> 28:05.683
<i>Two sons.</i>

28:07.852 --> 28:09.813
<i>Two years ago I delivered</i>

28:09.896 --> 28:13.233
<i>a stillborn baby girl.</i>

28:13.316 --> 28:17.237
<i>The light in the room</i>
<i>was very harsh.</i>

28:17.320 --> 28:19.989
<i>Very hard.</i>

28:21.741 --> 28:24.869
<i>Very hard.</i>

28:27.497 --> 28:30.750
<i>I hate the paint colors I chose</i>
<i>when we remodeled,</i>

28:30.834 --> 28:34.796
<i>and I hate</i>
<i>the living room drapes.</i>

28:34.879 --> 28:37.799
<i>I hate our cars.</i>

28:37.882 --> 28:41.094
<i>I wish that I didn't have</i>
<i>all of the things that I have</i>

28:41.177 --> 28:43.972
<i>and instead had</i>
<i>different things.</i>

28:44.055 --> 28:46.850
<i>I'm afraid of spiders</i>
<i>and horses.</i>

28:48.226 --> 28:50.270
<i>WARM FEMALE VOICE:</i>
<i>Yes, we know.</i>

28:53.565 --> 28:55.692
Where am I?

28:55.775 --> 28:58.027
<i>WARM FEMALE VOICE:</i>
<i>Are you comfortable?</i>

28:59.696 --> 29:02.615
Yes. Thank you.

29:04.117 --> 29:07.620
<i>Please do not make</i>
<i>any individualized,</i>

29:07.704 --> 29:10.081
<i>threatening movements.</i>

29:12.041 --> 29:13.835
Threatening?

29:13.918 --> 29:17.839
You're not afraid of me,
are you?

29:19.716 --> 29:21.968
<i>Are you comfortable?</i>

29:23.887 --> 29:27.682
Yes. Thank you.

29:29.934 --> 29:32.479
But why are you afraid of me?

29:34.439 --> 29:36.232
<i>WARM FEMALE VOICE:</i>
<i>We are afraid of how often</i>

29:36.316 --> 29:40.528
<i>you change your minds,</i>
<i>and so unexpectedly.</i>

29:40.612 --> 29:45.492
But surely you change
your mind sometimes.

29:45.575 --> 29:47.202
Don't you?

29:47.285 --> 29:51.623
<i>Ours is a single shared mind.</i>

29:51.706 --> 29:54.584
<i>To change it would require</i>
<i>the same energy needed</i>

29:54.667 --> 29:59.547
<i>to reverse the flow of your</i>
<i>so-called Mississippi River.</i>

30:01.341 --> 30:06.054
One mind. That doesn't sound
very democratic.

30:06.137 --> 30:08.765
<i>In a democracy,</i>
<i>half the population</i>

30:08.848 --> 30:11.559
<i>wants something different</i>
<i>than what they're getting.</i>

30:11.643 --> 30:14.229
<i>We've seen how that can go.</i>

30:14.312 --> 30:16.523
You're talking about Earth.

30:16.606 --> 30:18.733
<i>What's left of it.</i>

30:19.984 --> 30:22.529
You've been watching us?

30:22.612 --> 30:23.905
<i>Yes.</i>

30:23.988 --> 30:26.574
<i>Since first we heard</i>
<i>your radios.</i>

30:26.658 --> 30:29.077
<i>Nineteen hundred</i>
<i>and forty-five,</i>

30:29.160 --> 30:31.538
<i>the United States defeat Japan.</i>

30:31.621 --> 30:34.457
<i>Nineteen hundred</i>
<i>and sixty-five,</i>

30:34.541 --> 30:39.629
<i>the Beatles defeat</i>
<i>the son of your God, and so on.</i>

30:39.712 --> 30:42.757
Well, no, that's not
exactly right.

30:42.840 --> 30:46.052
<i>And then, in your 1950s, when</i>
<i>you started sending pictures,</i>

30:46.135 --> 30:48.137
<i>we watched.</i>

30:48.221 --> 30:52.600
<i>The trials of your kings,</i>
<i>the collapse of your towers.</i>

30:52.684 --> 30:55.770
<i>We studied the applause</i>
<i>of studio audiences,</i>

30:55.853 --> 30:59.482
<i>hoping it was evidence</i>
<i>of a single, shared mind.</i>

30:59.566 --> 31:02.068
<i>You can imagine our</i>
<i>disappointment when we learned</i>

31:02.151 --> 31:06.739
<i>it was artificial and canned,</i>
<i>like your diet colas.</i>

31:08.700 --> 31:10.618
<i>But more than anything else,</i>

31:10.702 --> 31:13.621
<i>we studied</i>
<i>your television commercials.</i>

31:13.705 --> 31:15.290
<i>We struggled to understand</i>

31:15.373 --> 31:18.459
<i>what was important to you,</i>
<i>what you loved.</i>

31:18.543 --> 31:22.088
<i>What you wanted, what</i>
<i>you needed, and why, so often,</i>

31:22.171 --> 31:24.382
<i>they weren't the same thing.</i>

31:26.843 --> 31:31.306
{\an8}You have all of this
unbelievable technology,

31:31.389 --> 31:34.601
{\an8}and all you've been doing
is watching television?

31:34.684 --> 31:36.811
<i>Specifically,</i>
<i>we have been watching</i>

31:36.894 --> 31:39.439
<i>your television commercials,</i>
<i>yes.</i>

31:39.522 --> 31:44.986
{\an8}But we don't even watch our
television commercials anymore.

31:45.069 --> 31:49.657
{\an8}We've, I don't know, evolved.

31:49.741 --> 31:51.826
{\an8}We skip right past them.

31:51.909 --> 31:55.496
<i>It's true, you have evolved.</i>

31:55.580 --> 31:58.041
<i>Commercials now grow</i>
<i>in the rich soil</i>

31:58.124 --> 32:01.336
<i>of your unconscious minds.</i>

32:01.419 --> 32:04.339
And that matters to you?

32:04.422 --> 32:08.217
<i>It only matters</i>
<i>that humans are stopped.</i>

32:08.301 --> 32:10.219
But...

32:10.303 --> 32:12.639
Okay.

32:12.722 --> 32:15.558
But what did I ever do?

32:15.642 --> 32:18.353
I'm not in charge
of anything, or...

32:18.436 --> 32:21.856
any governments
or countries or...

32:21.939 --> 32:25.860
<i>The Kanamit understands that a</i>
<i>human being is most vulnerable</i>

32:25.943 --> 32:29.322
<i>when it perceives</i>
<i>a lack of something.</i>

32:29.405 --> 32:31.157
<i>All you ever did</i>
<i>is want something</i>

32:31.240 --> 32:34.744
<i>other than</i>
<i>what you already had.</i>

32:34.827 --> 32:37.163
But that's anyone.

32:37.246 --> 32:38.373
That's anyone around here.

32:38.456 --> 32:40.249
That's, that's Ellen Jones,

32:40.333 --> 32:43.044
that's Marge Stevens
from right next-door.

32:43.127 --> 32:46.089
<i>But your wanting</i>
<i>is powered by grief.</i>

32:46.172 --> 32:48.383
<i>Like the great glittering</i>
<i>cities of your world,</i>

32:48.466 --> 32:51.761
<i>we can see your wanting</i>
<i>from space.</i>

32:51.844 --> 32:55.473
My grief doesn't make
television commercials.

32:59.352 --> 33:04.774
So you've been... monitoring us?

33:06.776 --> 33:12.365
Watching our commercials
so you can see...

33:12.448 --> 33:15.076
what makes us weak?

33:17.787 --> 33:19.789
So you can what?

33:21.332 --> 33:23.334
Invade us or something?

33:28.840 --> 33:30.091
(gasps)

33:32.218 --> 33:35.179
The EGG.

33:35.263 --> 33:40.435
You know what it is, don't you?

33:40.518 --> 33:43.438
<i>Of course I know what it is.</i>

33:43.521 --> 33:45.940
<i>Who do you think laid it?</i>

33:46.023 --> 33:49.861
<i>Who do you think</i>
<i>laid all of them?</i>

33:52.071 --> 33:54.157
♪<i> Sunshine, lollipops</i>
<i>and rainbows...</i> ♪

33:54.240 --> 33:57.952
{\an5}-Yeah!
<i>-The idea wasn't ours,</i>
<i>of course.</i>

33:58.035 --> 34:00.413
<i>The idea for the EGG was yours,</i>

34:00.496 --> 34:02.623
<i>-Mrs. Warren.</i>
-Yeah, yeah, yeah, yeah, yeah.

34:02.707 --> 34:04.041
(whoops)

34:04.125 --> 34:05.877
(tires screech)

34:05.960 --> 34:07.086
♪<i> And I feel...</i> ♪

34:07.170 --> 34:08.795
-(music stops)
-(chuckles)

34:08.880 --> 34:11.340
<i>WARM FEMALE VOICE: So that</i>
<i>everything could be okay again,</i>

34:11.424 --> 34:14.969
<i>and this time okay forever.</i>

34:15.052 --> 34:18.306
<i>And that's really</i>
<i>all we're doing.</i>

34:18.389 --> 34:21.476
<i>Everything will indeed</i>
<i>be okay again.</i>

34:21.559 --> 34:23.978
-Uh-uh. Okay...
<i>-Especially because</i>

34:24.061 --> 34:27.315
<i>there won't be</i>
<i>any human beings around</i>

34:27.398 --> 34:29.942
<i>to change their minds about it.</i>

34:30.025 --> 34:31.777
(snarling)

34:31.860 --> 34:34.572
Uh-oh--
oh, that's not very nice.

34:34.655 --> 34:35.656
-(crunching)
-Oh, God!

34:35.739 --> 34:37.324
(screaming)

34:37.408 --> 34:39.409
(loud pop)

34:57.553 --> 34:59.555
(birds chirping)

35:04.894 --> 35:06.896
♪ ♪

35:32.296 --> 35:34.298
Hello?

35:38.469 --> 35:40.513
Excuse me?

35:42.515 --> 35:46.185
I wonder if you can tell me
what time it is on Earth.

35:49.230 --> 35:52.441
I'd like to go back now, please.

35:52.525 --> 35:54.694
I'd like to go home.

35:54.777 --> 35:56.696
<i>You won't be able</i>
<i>to stop anything.</i>

35:56.779 --> 36:01.409
<i>And here with us,</i>
<i>you'll be safe.</i>

36:01.492 --> 36:05.204
I don't care about that,
and I don't want to,

36:05.288 --> 36:08.416
for God's sake,
stay here with you.

36:08.499 --> 36:11.919
I just want to be at my
designated fulfillment center

36:12.003 --> 36:13.588
at my allotted hour
of fulfillment,

36:13.671 --> 36:16.048
